Topics covered in this episode: Mormon true crime, LDS family systems, religious abandonment, intergenerational trauma, forensic psychiatry history, women in early 20th century Mormonism, faith deconstruction, mental illness in the 1920s, early intervention in mental health, schizophrenia history, lobotomy history, Oakland California history, San Quentin.

